29/03/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The interior ministry announced it will need an additional 2.6m euros to step up measures against terrorism in line with a new government strategy. Interior Minister Georgi Petkanov said the funds would pay for the deployment of 300 additional policemen and 100 firemen at strategic public buildings, as well as for the purchase of new monitoring and security equipment. Petkanov added that the Bulgarian and Greek interior services have co-ordinated additional security measures to be introduced before and during the Summer Olympics in Athens. (Mediapool, bTV - 28/03/04)
